‚ÄúI start by clarifying requirements like data volume, latency, consistency, and SLAs.
I then design an event-driven, horizontally scalable system using distributed ingestion, stateless processing, and scalable storage.
Data is partitioned by time and key for parallelism, schemas and quality checks are enforced early, and fault tolerance is achieved using retries, checkpoints, and idempotent writes.
Finally, I optimize for cost using incremental processing, lifecycle policies, and strong observability to track freshness, reliability, and performance.‚Äù 

